transcription.text:
Speaker 1: Thanks Paul, Dr. Quinn speaking. How can I help you?

Speaker 2: I got an order of generic...

Speaker 1: ...medication from you, the Silbenafil.

Speaker 2: Okay.

Speaker 1: I didn't want it in the first place.

Speaker 2: I ordered it by accident.

Speaker 1: I was attempting to order the new Pfizer...

Speaker 2: Okay, I can just reship it for you, sir.

Speaker 1: That'd be an easy fix. I don't mind doing that for you.

Speaker 2: If you ordered the wrong thing, that's perfectly fine.

Speaker 1: I don't mind resh... I can reship it for you. That happens.

Speaker 2: So you were looking to get the AGV, correct?

Speaker 1: Pardon me?

Speaker 2: You were looking to get the AGV? The newest stuff that we have?

Speaker 1: Yes.

Speaker 2: Okay. Let me... I'll do you one better.

Speaker 1: I will fix your account so whenever you do reorder,

Speaker 2: that's what you will receive.

Speaker 1: And I'm going to send you out a replacement

Speaker 2: for the ones you've got there, here, right now.

Speaker 1: Okay? One moment. Give me a second.

Speaker 2: 100 milligrams, correct?

Speaker 1: Yes.

Speaker 2: Okay. One second.

Speaker 1: And as I stated too, I will update the account to...

Speaker 2: You know, so when you do reorder,

Speaker 1: it will be the same ones I'm sending out now.

Speaker 2: Okay.

Speaker 1: One second here.

Speaker 2: All right. You are all set, sir.

Speaker 1: Okay.

Speaker 2: Anything else that you need?

Speaker 1: No. So I just dump these?

Speaker 2: No. Or you can keep them as a backup, if you'd like.

Speaker 1: But essentially, yes, you could throw them away.

Speaker 2: Yeah.

Speaker 1: I stopped using these like 20 years ago and got...

Speaker 2: Yeah. No worries.

Speaker 1: So if you don't want to keep them as a backup,

Speaker 2: you could throw them, toss them out.

Speaker 1: But I just did reship that to you.

Speaker 2: Okay. Thank you.

Speaker 1: You are very welcome.

Speaker 2: Any other questions you might have or anything?

Speaker 1: No. That's great. Thank you.

Speaker 2: You're very welcome. You have a good day.
